# API Documentation

## User Registration

### Register a New User
To register a new user, send a POST request to the following endpoint:
http://127.0.0.1:8000/signup
This endpoint accepts the user's registration details and creates a new user account.


## User Authentication

### Obtain Authentication Token
To authenticate users and obtain an authentication token, send a POST request to the following endpoint:
http://127.0.0.1:8000/api-token-auth/


## Todo Management

### Get All Todos
To retrieve a list of all todos, send a GET request to the following endpoint:
http://127.0.0.1:8000/todos/



### Get Todo Details
To retrieve details of a specific todo, send a GET request to the following endpoint:
http://127.0.0.1:8000/todos/<todo_id>/
Replace `<todo_id>` with the ID of the todo you want to retrieve details for. This endpoint returns the details of the specified todo.



### Create Todo
To create a new todo, send a POST request to the following endpoint:
http://127.0.0.1:8000/todos/
This endpoint accepts the details of the new todo and creates it.



## Category Management

### Get All Categories
To retrieve a list of all categories, send a GET request to the following endpoint:



This endpoint returns a list of all categories.

### Get Category Details
To retrieve details of a specific category, send a GET request to the following endpoint:
http://127.0.0.1:8000/categories/<categories_id>

Replace `<category_id>` with the ID of the category you want to retrieve details for. This endpoint returns the details of the specified category.



### Create Category
To create a new category, send a POST request to the following endpoint:
http://127.0.0.1:8000/categories/
This endpoint accepts the details of the new category and creates it.


**Note:** All endpoints requiring authentication require a valid authentication token to be included in the request headers.






























